HEADWORD: Cohune palm
<hw>Cohune
palm</hw> }</mhw>. <ety>[Prob. fr. a native name in Honduras.]</ety>
<def>A Central and South American pinnate-leaved palm (<spn>Attalea
cohune</spn>), the very large and hard nuts of which are turned to make
fancy articles, and also yield an oil used as a substitute for coconut
oil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

